    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Deenanath Mangeshkar Hospital. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Surgeon to strengthen our Gwalior-based team.\n\nAbout Deenanath Mangeshkar Hospital:\nDeenanath Mangeshkar Hospital is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Referral bonus program\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Deenanath Mangeshkar Hospital!",
